+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01B6BY4rcccFy1gtpkh8ZTvM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Phase 1: Basic FIFO Queue\n     2→\n     3→Implement the core of the task queue: the ability to add tasks and retrieve them in first-in, first-out order.\n     4→\n     5→## Requirements\n     6→\n     7→- The queue should accept a payload (any data) when a task is added, and return a task object.\n     8→- Each task must have a unique identifier (e.g., UUID), a status, and a creation timestamp.\n     9→- New tasks start in a \"pending\" state.\n    10→- Retrieving the next task should return the oldest pending task and transition it to a \"processing\" state.\n    11→- If no tasks are available, retrieval should return `null`.\n    12→- There should be a way to check how many tasks are waiting.\n    13→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_016U2GrB2hq5XXPLkyrETPDh","session_id":"c224e1c2-6e95-4036-80b3-e4b2caf2cba3","uuid":"414bc1fa-e4bd-476b-9f4d-b0a7e189a428"}
