+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01DkT2nAZHMf4zXWSakiWibM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Fix H1**: The FIFO ordering issue. The `get()` comparator uses `availableAt` as a secondary sort, but for non-delayed tasks created at slightly different `Date.now()`, this can break FIFO. I need to use array index (insertion order) as the FIFO tiebreaker within same priority, and only use `availableAt` ordering when both tasks have explicit delays.\n\nActually, re-reading the Phase 4 spec more carefully: \"When multiple delayed tasks become available simultaneously, they should be ordered by availability time, then priority, then FIFO.\" This means the general ordering is: priority first, then for same-priority: availability time, then FIFO. The issue is that non-delayed tasks may have slightly different `availableAt` values. The fix is to make non-delayed tasks all share the same epoch (or use a counter for insertion order).\n\nThe cleanest fix: add an insertion sequence counter and use it for FIFO ordering instead of relying on array index + availableAt."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":638,"cache_read_input_tokens":64726,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":638},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c224e1c2-6e95-4036-80b3-e4b2caf2cba3","uuid":"ff0f09a2-7b38-4c94-8910-a1076ab97703"}
