+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Y3EpSdfsLmbxfTV5CZzCCu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue\n     2→\n     3→Add a dead letter queue (DLQ) to capture tasks that have permanently failed after exhausting all retries.\n     4→\n     5→## Requirements\n     6→\n     7→- When a task has no more retries left, it is automatically moved to a dead letter queue associated with its original queue.\n     8→- There should be a way to view all dead-lettered tasks for a given queue.\n     9→- Dead-lettered tasks should retain their error information and a count of how many times they failed.\n    10→- It should be possible to move a dead-lettered task back to its original queue for a fresh round of retries.\n    11→- There should be a way to clear all dead-lettered tasks for a queue.\n    12→- Each named queue has its own independent dead letter queue.\n    13→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_018nFx3xJFLPrF7Lr6vHXofY","session_id":"c224e1c2-6e95-4036-80b3-e4b2caf2cba3","uuid":"c0ed2ba7-3490-4605-a5f6-7bee1c74ad69"}
